{"name":"Tear 'em Ter Bits!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A truly enraged Ogryn is a terrible thing to behold, as childlike</p>\n<p>glee and enthusiasm gives way to something altogether fiercer</p>\n<p>and more primal. Enemies that provoke an Ogryn into such a</p>\n<p>state find only the small mercy that they do not have to endure</p>\n<p>such a terror for long, although their surviving comrades are</p>\n<p>likely to remember the grisly scene for the rest of their lives.</p>\n<p>Once per encounter, when this character inflicts Critical</p>\n<p>Damage on an enemy by dealing Damage in excess of the</p>\n<p>enemy&rsquo;s Wounds, he may spend a Fate Point to instantly slay</p>\n<p>his foe in an exceptionally gruesome manner. The enemy</p>\n<p>may be literally pulled apart by the Ogryn&rsquo;s blows, cleaved</p>\n<p>into bits, or dismembered in some other terrifying display</p>\n<p>of might. He gains the Fear (2) Trait against all foes who</p>\n<p>witnessed this savage display until the end of the encounter.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ogryn, Strength 50","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Strength, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"tearemterbits","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"melee, ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jQsegB2Q3aqeN2yC"}
{"name":"Attend the Machine Spirits","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The character has passed some of his extensive</p>\n<p>technological knowledge on to his Comrade, enabling the</p>\n<p>Comrade to assist with complex activation rites and the</p>\n<p>careful calibration of complex technologies. When assisted</p>\n<p>by his Comrade, the character can more easily accomplish</p>\n<p>anything from reinitialising the generatorium plant of a</p>\n<p>Leman Russ to performing pinpoint scans with an auspex.</p>\n<p>A Character can use this Order when he attempts to</p>\n<p>activate or operate a piece of technology that requires a Tech-</p>\n<p>Use Test. The character&rsquo;s Comrade assists him with the Test,</p>\n<p>granting the character a +10 bonus. The character&rsquo;s Comrade</p>\n<p>must be in Cohesion to enact this Order. This Order is usable</p>\n<p>with a Servitor Comrade.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Common Lore (Adeptus Mechanicus), Tech-Use +10","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"attendthemachinespirits","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ugls6fSup52xwQZO"}
{"name":"Honour the Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The character has ensured his comrade is well-versed</p>\n<p>in the maintenance and care of all weapons in the arsenal of</p>\n<p>the Imperial Guard, so that he may ensure that their machine</p>\n<p>spirits are kept in proper order. When excessive use or hazardous</p>\n<p>circumstances rile the spirits of his squad&rsquo;s weapons, he may send</p>\n<p>his comrade to undo the harm with the briefest of signals.</p>\n<p>The character may issue this Order whenever a character</p>\n<p>in his squad (including himself) is suffering from a weapon</p>\n<p>Jam. His Comrade immediately repairs the Jam without a</p>\n<p>Test, as long as the character with the Jammed weapon is</p>\n<p>within five meters. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be within</p>\n<p>communication range to enact this Order. This Order is</p>\n<p>usable with a Servitor Comrade.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Common Lore (Adeptus Mechanicus), Common Lore (Tech)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"honourtheweapon","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HArSCL4YdpRiihwh"}
{"name":"Preserve the Burning Chariot","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>The loss of valuable technology to war is an</p>\n<p>unfortunate and inevitable reality for its devoted caretakers,</p>\n<p>but they nonetheless drill ceaselessly in all possible means of</p>\n<p>preserving it against harm for as long as possible. Through</p>\n<p>careful study of the volatile war spirits of armoured vehicles,</p>\n<p>the character is able to direct his comrade to put out fires</p>\n<p>aboard any vehicle aboard which they travel.</p>\n<p>This Order can be used to direct a Comrade to assist in</p>\n<p>fire-fighting efforts, or to direct him to put out a fire while the</p>\n<p>character performs other Actions. If the Comrade is assisting his</p>\n<p>controlling Player Character in putting out a fire, he grants the</p>\n<p>relevant Test a +20 bonus. A Comrade that is being directed</p>\n<p>to put out a fire on his own does so if the controlling Player</p>\n<p>Character passes a Hard (&ndash;20) Command Test. Note that the</p>\n<p>difficulty of this Test is due to being on board a burning vehicle,</p>\n<p>rather than in addition to that penalty. This Order is usable with</p>\n<p>a Servitor Comrade.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Adeptus Mechanicus, Any Essential Repair Skill +10 (see page 281 of the O nly W ar Core Rulebook)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"preservetheburningchariot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eGYUpfpr8Wxu3WFn"}
{"name":"Cleanse with Fire!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The character has ensured his Comrade is equipped</p>\n<p>with the necessary tools to create and maintain his battle-</p>\n<p>pyres. Thanks to these efforts, the comrade carries a hand</p>\n<p>flamer, burning brazier, censer full of igniferous fluids, or</p>\n<p>similar tool of cleansing and purification. When commanded,</p>\n<p>the Comrade joins his effort to the fiery assaults of the</p>\n<p>character to bring burning light into the darkness of enemy</p>\n<p>forces, to ensure its continued flame.</p>\n<p>The character can issue this Order whenever any enemy</p>\n<p>within 10 meters of the character&rsquo;s Comrade is on fire. Until</p>\n<p>this character&rsquo;s next Turn, the chosen foe suffers a &ndash;20</p>\n<p>penalty on any Tests to extinguish its flames, and suffers an</p>\n<p>additional 1d5 Damage from the effects of the Flame Quality</p>\n<p>whenever it affects him. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in</p>\n<p>Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Scholastic Lore (Imperial Creed), Weapon Training (Flame)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"cleansewithfire","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6d4skFkCUcBtzWcX"}
{"name":"Cower Not before the Enemy!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action)</p>\n<p>The Imperium has no room for shirkers or the</p>\n<p>dereliction of duty, and it is one of the duties of a battle</p>\n<p>preacher to see that every soldier gives his all in the God-</p>\n<p>Emperor&rsquo;s wars. Hesitation and flight have no place among</p>\n<p>the actions of a right-thinking soldier, and the fiery rhetoric</p>\n<p>of the Adeptus Ministorum serves to remind even the most</p>\n<p>petrified warrior of his duty to the Imperial Guard.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character must make a Challenging</p>\n<p>(+0) Charm or Command Test. If he succeeds, all Comrades</p>\n<p>in communication range immediately overcome any ongoing</p>\n<p>Fear or Pinning effects they are suffering. They can act</p>\n<p>normally in subsequent Turns.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ministorum Priest or 10+ Insanity Points","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"cowernotbeforetheenemy","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1PVc2tDUzUgtRxwq"}
{"name":"Do Not Wait for Death!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Free Action)</p>\n<p>There is no mortal figure held in higher esteem across</p>\n<p>the Imperium than the warrior-martyr, who deals death as easily</p>\n<p>as he accepts it. The Adeptus Ministorum trains its preachers to</p>\n<p>seek to evoke this ideal among even the most hesitant. Those</p>\n<p>who are most skilled in rhetoric can inspire feats of near-</p>\n<p>suicidal bravery from those around them, encouraging them to</p>\n<p>lay aside all doubt in the prosecution of their cause.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character must make a Hard (&ndash;20)</p>\n<p>Charm or Command Test. If he succeeds, all Comrades in</p>\n<p>communication range leap to the fore of the battle, intercepting</p>\n<p>blows meant for their brethren without regard for their own</p>\n<p>lives. Until the end of this character&rsquo;s next Turn, as long as</p>\n<p>a character&rsquo;s Comrade is in cohesion with him, the Comrade</p>\n<p>is struck instead of the character with any attack that would</p>\n<p>have hit the character. However, if the Attack Test result was a</p>\n<p>double, the Attack hits the character and is resolved normally.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Command +10, Ministorum Priest","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"donotwaitfordeath","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aaWgKbpl1Mr48tYP"}
{"name":"Let the Creed Resound!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Passive</p>\n<p>Even the best orator must be heard in order to have</p>\n<p>an effect&mdash;a requirement often difficult to meet on a chaotic</p>\n<p>battlefield. To overcome this barrier, the character has trained</p>\n<p>his Comrade to relay his words so that they may be more</p>\n<p>easily passed through the ranks of the Imperial Guard.</p>\n<p>As long as this character&rsquo;s Comrade is in Cohesion with</p>\n<p>him, the character counts as being equipped with a Laud</p>\n<p>Hailer, and can affect up to twice the normal number of</p>\n<p>subjects with his Interaction Skill Tests. This effect stacks</p>\n<p>with Talents such as Master Orator.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Command +10, Ministorum Priest","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"letthecreedresound","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, priest","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HNEk4Ipb4yYbzMmy"}
{"name":"Cut Loose!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Ogryns are notorious among the quartermasters</p>\n<p>of the Imperial Guard for their prodigious expenditure of</p>\n<p>ammunition. They rarely, if ever, seem to grasp such concepts</p>\n<p>of &ldquo;burst fire&rdquo; or &ldquo;aiming,&rdquo; and sometimes unload full clips</p>\n<p>into empty air when startled. The most disciplined among</p>\n<p>their number (for what such a label is worth), and others</p>\n<p>who work with these massive warriors, can occasionally</p>\n<p>manage to convince their Comrades to keep the barrels</p>\n<p>of their ripper guns pointing directly towards the enemy.</p>\n<p>Though they cannot curb their Comrades&rsquo; tendency to over-</p>\n<p>expend ammunition, this habit can still be made to serve the</p>\n<p>Imperium, as the wild hail of bullets makes it difficult to</p>\n<p>evade any more carefully placed fire.</p>\n<p>As part of this order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade wildly</p>\n<p>unloads as many shots as possible; until the end of the Turn,</p>\n<p>enemies must re-roll successful Dodge Tests made to avoid</p>\n<p>attacks by the character. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be</p>\n<p>within Cohesion for him to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Strength 35, Ogryn Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"cutloose","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yTXq9F1DcJ0ZR767"}
{"name":"Get Behind Me!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Although Ogryns are famously protective of their</p>\n<p>brothers-in-arms, they are not similarly renowned for taking</p>\n<p>initiative in their defence of these wards. It usually falls to</p>\n<p>an Ogryn&rsquo;s squad mates to determine how his strength and</p>\n<p>bulk can best shield them in any given situation. However,</p>\n<p>there are exceptions&mdash;Ogryns with the ability to think on</p>\n<p>their feet better than most, who have mastered the art of</p>\n<p>sheltering their smaller and weaker Comrades behind an</p>\n<p>imposing wall of muscle.</p>\n<p>The Ogryn&rsquo;s Comrade moves behind his massive ally.</p>\n<p>While sheltered in this way, the Comrade is not hit by attacks</p>\n<p>(and if an attack would hit him, such as on a result of doubles,</p>\n<p>it hits the Ogryn instead) and immediately recovers from the</p>\n<p>effects of Fear and Pinning. This effect lasts until the Ogryn</p>\n<p>or his Comrade moves. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in</p>\n<p>Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Toughness 50, Ogryn, non-Ogryn Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Toughness, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"getbehindme","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6Kaq8IQ8uL1bvfnh"}
{"name":"Take 'em Down!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The great strength of an Ogryn&rsquo;s blows can slay</p>\n<p>almost any foe, but sometimes particularly nimble foes can</p>\n<p>still prove difficult to kill as they evade strike after strike.</p>\n<p>An Ogryn frustrated in this way can call upon the aid of</p>\n<p>his Comrade to help pin down a mobile foe or bowl the</p>\n<p>enemy over. Once put on the ground and slammed by the</p>\n<p>full weight of an Ogryn moments later, the enemy rarely</p>\n<p>gets back up.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade moves to</p>\n<p>engage one foe within his Charge Move distance. The target</p>\n<p>must make a Challenging (+0) Dodge Test or be knocked</p>\n<p>Prone. This character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in Cohesion to</p>\n<p>enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Strength 45, Ogryn","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Strength, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"takeemdown","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uqI9PmrJtKhSs8zO"}
{"name":"Thump 'em!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>If the power of one Ogryn striking a target is deadly,</p>\n<p>then surely any two Ogryns that manage to coordinate their</p>\n<p>blows are a force to be reckoned with. Although no Ogryn</p>\n<p>tolerates long hours of combat drills with anything resembling</p>\n<p>good grace, sometimes the basic concepts nevertheless sink</p>\n<p>into their thick skulls with startling effect.</p>\n<p>The next melee attack Action the character undertake</p>\n<p>inflicts an additional +4 Damage and gains the Concussive</p>\n<p>(0) Quality. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in Cohesion to</p>\n<p>enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ogryn, Ogryn Comrade, Frenzy","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Weapon Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"thumpem","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ogryn","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4EnAdQJ6RFcQ7NRt"}
{"name":"Distance, Elevation, Wind Speed?","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>At the utmost extremes of a weapon&rsquo;s effective</p>\n<p>firing distance, even the slightest variable in environmental</p>\n<p>conditions can throw off the accuracy of a shot. Hitting a</p>\n<p>target at these ranges is as much logic and mathematics as aim,</p>\n<p>but a well-trained Comrade can help the character quickly</p>\n<p>determine any adjustments necessary to place his shot.</p>\n<p>On any Turn in which the character&rsquo;s Comrade has enacted</p>\n<p>this Order, the character&rsquo;s ranged weapons treat targets out to</p>\n<p>three times their weapon&rsquo;s Range as being at Long Range,</p>\n<p>and treat targets beyond four times their weapon&rsquo;s Range as</p>\n<p>being at Extreme Range. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in</p>\n<p>Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Perception 35, Ratling Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"dews","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ST1AOrBXY5qVJkqp"}
{"name":"Keep Them Off Balance!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The best Ratling fighters are masters of misdirection</p>\n<p>and improvisation, and they often pass these skills on to their</p>\n<p>Comrades. Working as a well-honed team, the character and</p>\n<p>his Comrade create openings for each other&rsquo;s attacks, and</p>\n<p>then ruthlessly exploit them.</p>\n<p>This Order can only be issued after the character has</p>\n<p>inflicted Damage an enemy with an attack. When the</p>\n<p>character&rsquo;s Comrade enacts this Order, the enemy Damaged</p>\n<p>by the character&rsquo;s attack must make a Challenging (+0)</p>\n<p>Toughness Test; if he fails, he is Stunned for one Round. The</p>\n<p>character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Agility 40, Ratling Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"keepthemoffbalance","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rSLCnfySAa6p0kzO"}
{"name":"Hostiles Detected!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Sweeping Order (Special)</p>\n<p>The keen eyes of a Ratling have more uses than simply</p>\n<p>bringing down distant targets. The character may issue this</p>\n<p>Order when one or more of the other Player Characters have</p>\n<p>been Surprised. All Comrades affected by this Order immediately</p>\n<p>spend a Half Action to benefit from cover as if they had been</p>\n<p>issued the Take Cover! Generic Order, even if their controlling</p>\n<p>Player Character was Surprised and cannot act.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Perception 40, Ratling","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"hostilesdetected","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"c8SwNuptiNH7aBus"}
{"name":"They'll Never Know What hit Them!","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half or Full Action)</p>\n<p>The character has trained his Comrade to cover his</p>\n<p>tracks, set up blinds, and provide diversions for any searching</p>\n<p>eyes from the enemy camp. When working together, the two</p>\n<p>soldiers can pass unseen through nearly any terrain to arrive</p>\n<p>at the perfect sniper&rsquo;s perch, then rain shot after shot onto</p>\n<p>their vulnerable targets without being spotted.</p>\n<p>As part of this Action, the character&rsquo;s Comrade must</p>\n<p>expend a Half Action, or a Full Action if the character</p>\n<p>has made an attack since the beginning of his last Turn.</p>\n<p>All attempts to spot the character or his Comrade suffer</p>\n<p>a &ndash;20 penalty during any Round in which the character&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>Comrade has enacted this Order. This Order can be</p>\n<p>issued outside of combat, in which case its effects can be</p>\n<p>assumed to apply until the Comrade ceases to work at</p>\n<p>providing concealment. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be</p>\n<p>in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ratling, Ratling Comrade, Stealth +10","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"tnkwht","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, ratling","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1kYOf5d1fenMnOUe"}
{"name":"Armour negation Protocols","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The necessities of war require the Imperium to not</p>\n<p>only muster every weapon in its arsenal, but to make weapons</p>\n<p>of its tools if this proves insufficient. Although breacher</p>\n<p>servitors are primarily intended for use in mining operations,</p>\n<p>the powerful drills that make them capable of piercing the</p>\n<p>roots of mountains are just as capable of punching through</p>\n<p>the armour of enemy troops should their master wish it.</p>\n<p>The character&rsquo;s melee attacks gain +5 Penetration until the</p>\n<p>end of the Turn. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be in Cohesion</p>\n<p>to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Lathe-pattern Breacher Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Weapon Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"armournegationprotocol","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"51hmampc93M5UQnc"}
{"name":"Attack Pattern Gladius Ultra","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The primary function of a Clipaeus-class Combat</p>\n<p>Servitor is to defend its assigned master, a goal which it</p>\n<p>pursues with ruthless efficiency. Once cleared for action by</p>\n<p>a brief directive, it unleashes an unrelenting series of brutal</p>\n<p>jabs and thrusts with its potent electro-gladius, slaying or</p>\n<p>incapacitating any who presume to threaten its charge.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade makes</p>\n<p>a Standard Melee Attack Action against a target within</p>\n<p>melee range. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be within</p>\n<p>communication range to enact this Order. If it is also in</p>\n<p>Cohesion, it gains a +10 bonus to its Weapon Skill Test.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Clipaeus-class Combat Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"none","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"apgu","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"g6OtcXUrJkDDtY4w"}
{"name":"Attack Pattern Pugnis Furioso","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The Pugnis-class Combat Servitor is a common sight</p>\n<p>on battlefields throughout the galaxy, as are the torn and</p>\n<p>battered corpses left crushed by its heavy servo-fists. Tech-</p>\n<p>Priests assigned to combat duties quickly learn how best to</p>\n<p>coordinate their attacks with the massive strength behind these</p>\n<p>blows. Those with the resources and training to control several</p>\n<p>such servitors find some basic adjustments to the servitors&rsquo;</p>\n<p>default attack patterns provide even more impressive results</p>\n<p>The character gains a +5 bonus to Weapon Skill Tests</p>\n<p>for Melee Attacks and inflicts an additional +2 Damage</p>\n<p>with melee attacks until the end of the Turn. If the character</p>\n<p>controls multiple Pugnis-class Servitor Comrades, he may issue</p>\n<p>this Order to any number of them, gaining an additional +5</p>\n<p>bonus to Weapon Skill Tests and inflicting an additional +1</p>\n<p>Damage for each Servitor taking part in the Order beyond the</p>\n<p>first. The Servitors must be in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Pugnis-class Combat Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"none","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"appf","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6sB0bO4VBWsgkTGa"}
{"name":"Bastion Protocols","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>Many Tech-Priests add basic bodyguard protocols to</p>\n<p>the servitors they control, so that their lives and knowledge</p>\n<p>can be preserved at a minimal cost in resources.</p>\n<p>The character orders his Servitor to protect him; until</p>\n<p>he gives the Servitor the signal to stand down as a Free</p>\n<p>Action, whenever an attack would strike him, it strikes the</p>\n<p>Servitor, and vice-versa. The Servitor must be in Cohesion</p>\n<p>to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"bastionprotocols","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Hdmg5yy6qyj5XUIW"}
{"name":"Combat Mnemo-Analysis","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>The addition of mnemo-analysis capabilities is a</p>\n<p>favoured choice among the myriad common adjustments and</p>\n<p>recalibrations possible for servitors among the Tech-Priests</p>\n<p>who serve with the Imperial Guard. When outfitted with</p>\n<p>the appropriate optical enhancements and other upgrades, a</p>\n<p>servitor becomes capable of providing valuable metrics on the</p>\n<p>combat style and manoeuvres of any enemy on the battlefield.</p>\n<p>This data is provided to its master in a number of arcane ways,</p>\n<p>from brief bursts of Techna-Lingua code phrases to vox-</p>\n<p>transmissions sent to a matching mnemo-implant installed</p>\n<p>in the Tech-Priest&rsquo;s skull. Once gathered, this information</p>\n<p>makes it all but impossible for the enemy under analysis to</p>\n<p>surprise the Tech-Priest or act in a way he cannot counter.</p>\n<p>When this Order is enacted, the character designates</p>\n<p>a single foe within his line of sight as the target. Until the</p>\n<p>beginning of the character&rsquo;s next Turn, the target suffers a</p>\n<p>&ndash;20 penalty to Dodge and Parry Tests to evade the character&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>attacks, and the character gains a +20 bonus to Dodge and</p>\n<p>Parry Tests to avoid the target&rsquo;s attacks. The character&rsquo;s</p>\n<p>Comrade must be in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Scrutiny +10, Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"combatmnemoanalysis","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"suBh1yU7AzNyi23N"}
{"name":"Emergency Overrides","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>As servitors become damaged working in the</p>\n<p>hazardous conditions of the battlefield, the efficiency of</p>\n<p>their masters drop drastically. A damaged servitor is more a</p>\n<p>hindrance than an aid, which is an intolerable situation to</p>\n<p>the demands of the Imperial war machine. For this reason,</p>\n<p>many among the Adeptus Mechanicus integrate emergency</p>\n<p>compensators and power sources into their servitors to allow</p>\n<p>them to serve through severe damage. These measures can</p>\n<p>be more destructive in the long term than the damage they</p>\n<p>mitigate, but this trade off is often deemed acceptable in the</p>\n<p>heat of battle.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character issuing it must</p>\n<p>choose one of his Servitor Comrades who is Wounded and</p>\n<p>make a Routine (+20) Tech-Use Test. If he succeeds, the</p>\n<p>Comrade engages its fail-safes and can act as if it was not</p>\n<p>Wounded or Dead until the end of the encounter, regardless</p>\n<p>of any further damage it suffers. At the end of the encounter,</p>\n<p>the Tech-Priest must make a Hard (&ndash;20) Tech-Use Test</p>\n<p>to compensate for this dangerous straining of its systems;</p>\n<p>if he succeeds, the Servitor becomes Wounded, but if he</p>\n<p>fails, it collapses into a pile of scrap and blood, dead and</p>\n<p>unsuitable for further use. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be</p>\n<p>in Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Servitor Comrade, Tech-Use +10","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"emergencyoverrides","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XcUSOEONdyQTQBDM"}
{"name":"Flame Sweep Initiation","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Half Action)</p>\n<p>The Imperial Guard typically relies on dedicated</p>\n<p>weapon specialists trained in the use of flame weapons to</p>\n<p>flush enemies from their bunkers and trenches, and to put</p>\n<p>fire to their lesser fortifications. When assisted by Incendio-</p>\n<p>class Gun Servitors, this task can be accomplished where such</p>\n<p>specialists are unavailable, or when they must perform other</p>\n<p>battlefield roles. Gun servitors are an efficient alternative to</p>\n<p>ordinary troopers, who bring with them the concerns of</p>\n<p>morale or frailty common to mortal flesh.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade makes a</p>\n<p>Standard Ranged Attack Action with its integrated flamer.</p>\n<p>Enemies in the area of effect can attempt to avoid the attack</p>\n<p>with a Challenging (+0) Agility Test, as normal.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Incendio-class Gun Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"none","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"flamesweepinitiation","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Rw9LBOVluJ0WJVHx"}
{"name":"Heavy Firepower Assault","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Attack Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>The big guns of the Imperial Guard are numberless,</p>\n<p>from the vaunted Deathstrike Missile Launchers and the</p>\n<p>mighty Earthshaker batteries of the artillery regiments, all</p>\n<p>the way down to the man-portable weapons carried by the</p>\n<p>heavy weapon teams of an infantry squad. However, all of</p>\n<p>these weapons have their origins in the forges of the Adeptus</p>\n<p>Mechanicus, and they have their own delivery platforms to use.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade takes a</p>\n<p>Standard Ranged Attack Action, Semi-Auto Burst Action, or</p>\n<p>Full Auto Burst Action with one weapon against a target within</p>\n<p>range of that weapon. The character&rsquo;s Comrade must be within</p>\n<p>Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Jovian-pattern Gun Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"none","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"heavyfirepowerassault","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"93wGAuBd5YrB2pMX"}
{"name":"Heavy Suppression Barrage","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Attack Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>Gun Servitors can make use of their integrated</p>\n<p>weapons as easily as a trained gunner. Servitors equipped</p>\n<p>with the appropriate weaponry can lay down withering hails</p>\n<p>of suppressive fire unmatched by the common soldiery.</p>\n<p>This Order can only be issued to Servitor Comrades</p>\n<p>outfitted with a weapon capable of semi- or fully automatic</p>\n<p>fire. As part of this Order, the character designates a kill zone,</p>\n<p>which is any general area, such as a corridor or tree line, that</p>\n<p>encompasses a 45 degree arc in the direction the Comrade</p>\n<p>is facing. Then, as part of the Order, the Comrade unleashes</p>\n<p>Suppressing Fire as detailed on page 248 of the O nly W ar</p>\n<p>Core Rulebook.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Jovian-pattern Gun Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"heavysuppressionbarrage","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1o9YctMsvX00wh05"}
{"name":"Interdiction Manoeuvre Pattern","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>The advanced bodyguard protocols imprinted in the</p>\n<p>Clipaeus-class of servitors grants them unparalleled ability to</p>\n<p>respond to approaching threats. When placed on alert status</p>\n<p>by the commands of their master, they wait for attackers to</p>\n<p>approach, then explode into motion with a swift and deadly</p>\n<p>pre-emptive strike.</p>\n<p>The character gives his Servitor the directive to defend</p>\n<p>him. Until the beginning of the character&rsquo;s next Turn,</p>\n<p>the first time an enemy approaches within 5 metres of</p>\n<p>the character, his Servitor moves to intercept and makes a</p>\n<p>Challenging (+0) Weapon Skill Test. If it succeeds, it</p>\n<p>inflicts a single hit on the target with its electro-gladius.</p>\n<p>If the approaching character was making a Charge Action</p>\n<p>against the character, his attack now targets the Servitor</p>\n<p>instead of his original target. The Servitor must be in</p>\n<p>Cohesion to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Clipaeus-class Combat Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Weapon Skill, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"interdictionmanoeuvrepattern","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"V6skQ4ehLts2Qikl"}
{"name":"Precision Firepower Delivery","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>Type: Attack Order (Full Action)</p>\n<p>After extensive service, many Gun Servitors end</p>\n<p>up modified extensively with enhanced targeting protocols</p>\n<p>and data uplinks that enable pinpoint accuracy, allowing</p>\n<p>them to unleash their armament to devastating effect.</p>\n<p>The enhancements made to facilitate this are often unique</p>\n<p>to each servitor, as they must be integrated carefully with</p>\n<p>consideration to its optical implants and any relevant</p>\n<p>cybernetic systems installed in its master.</p>\n<p>This Order may only be issued to Servitor Comrades</p>\n<p>outfitted with a weapon capable of firing single shots.</p>\n<p>As part of this Order, the character&rsquo;s Comrade makes a</p>\n<p>Standard Ranged Attack Action against a target within the</p>\n<p>range of its integrated heavy weapon, which is used for</p>\n<p>the attack. The Servitor must be in communication range</p>\n<p>to enact this Order.</p>","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"0","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Jovian-pattern Gun Servitor Comrade","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"precisionfirepowerdelivery","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"comrade, servitor","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"A5OzI3kNOtb41VPB"}
